{com}. /* *************************************************************************** *
> *                                               WFP DRC In Camp Refugees Targeting                                         * 
> *                                                                                                                                                          *
> *  PURPOSE:                     Data Append, Cleaning & Proxy Variable Construction        *              
> *  DATE:                                Dec 15, 2022                                                                               *
> *  LATEST UPDATE:               Jan 10, 2023                                                                                       *
> *                 
> ********************************************************************************
>         
>         ** OUTLINE:             PART 1: Prepare globals and define paths
>                                         PART 2: Set codebook template
>                                         PART 3: Variable creation
>                                         PART 4: Label variables
>                                         PART 5: Save dataset for analysis
>                                 
>         ** REQUIRES:    ${c -(}dataset{c )-}/DRC_BUR_noID_cleaned_revtarg.dta
>                                         ${c -(}dataset{c )-}/DRC_CAR_IC_noID_cleaned_revtarg.dta
>                                         ${c -(}dataset{c )-}/DRC_SSD_noID_cleaned_revtarg.dta
>                                         
>         ** CREATES:             ${c -(}dataset{c )-}/DRC_CAR_Inside_Camp_2021.dta
>                                         ${c -(}dataset{c )-}/DRC_CAR_Inside_Camp_2021.sav
>                                         "${c -(}output{c )-}/DRC_CAR_In&Out_Camp_2021.dta"
>                                         "${c -(}output{c )-}/DRC_CAR_In&Out_Camp_2021.sav"
>                                         
>         ** BUR
>         La méthodologie a consisté à interviewer la totalité des ménages réfugiés 
>         burundais des camps de Lusenda et Mulongwe (province Sud Kivu) et 
>         d'approfondir certaines thématiques avec un échantillon de 7 % (560) de la 
>         population choisi au hasard. Au total 7 873 ménages ont été retenus.
>         
>         ** CAR_IC
>         Au total, 1 450 ménages ont été sélectionnés grâce à un échantillonnage 
>         aléatoire stratifié et au final 1 328 ont été retenus.
>         
>         ** VULNERABILITY FRAMEWORK
>         No ECMEN data for Burundian (n = 560)
>         VulnerabilityCat_d_hv is the only full variable (the one we used for Outside camp)
>         
> *******************************************************************************/
. 
. * Harmonize settings across users
.     ieboilstart, v(13.0)

{res}{phang}{err:DISCLAIMER:} Due to how settings work in Stata, this command can only attempt to harmonize settings as much as possible across users, but no guarantee can be given that all commands will always behave identically unless the exact same version and type of Stata is used, with the same releases of user-contributed commands installed.{p_end}

{col 5}{ul:Settings set by this command:}{break}{col 5}clear all{break}{col 5}set maxvar {col 22}120000{col 28}, permanently{break}{col 5}set matsize {col 22}400{col 28}, permanently{break}{col 5}set niceness{col 22}5{col 28}, permanently{break}{col 5}set min_memory {col 22}0{col 28}, permanently{break}{col 5}set max_memory {col 22}.{col 28}, permanently{break}{col 5}set segmentsize  {col 22}32m{col 28}, permanently{break}{col 5}set more {col 22}off{col 28}, permanently{break}{col 5}pause {col 22}on{break}{col 5}set varabbrev {col 22}off{col 28}, permanently{break}{col 5}set type {col 22}float{col 28}, permanently

{phang}{err:IMPORTANT:} One important setting of this command – the Stata version – cannot be set inside the command due to how this setting works. The setting has been prepared by this command, and you only need to write `r(version)' after this command (include the apostrophes) for the version setting to be applied.{p_end}
{txt}
{com}.     `r(version)'
{txt}
{com}.         
. * Set scheme
.         set scheme plotplainblind
{txt}
{com}.         graph set window fontface "Times New Roman"
{txt}
{com}. 
. ********************************************************************************
. *                                               PART 1:  Prepare globals and define paths                          *
. ********************************************************************************
.         
. * add your directory below
.         display c(username)     // Get your username and add path to the working folder
{res}nicolewu
{txt}
{com}.          
. * set directories
. * ---------------       
.         global mac       1
{txt}
{com}.         global windows   0
{txt}
{com}. 
. * set the GD Folder
. if $mac {c -(}
.         global targeting  "/Users/nicolewu/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WorldFoodProgramme/General - T&P CO Support"
. {c )-}
{txt}
{com}. 
. if $windows {c -(}
.         global targeting  "C:/Users/Kareem.Sadik/OneDrive - World Food Programme/T&P CO Support/General"
. {c )-} 
{txt}
{com}. 
. * Subfolder globals
. * -----------------
.         gl DRC                  "${c -(}targeting{c )-}/DRC"
{txt}
{com}.         
.         gl dataset              "${c -(}DRC{c )-}/01_Data"        
{txt}
{com}.         gl dofile               "${c -(}DRC{c )-}/02_Code"
{txt}
{com}.         gl output               "${c -(}DRC{c )-}/03_Output"
{txt}
{com}.         gl instrument   "${c -(}DRC{c )-}/04_Instrument"
{txt}
{com}.         gl codebook             "${c -(}DRC{c )-}/05_Codebook"
{txt}
{com}. 
. ********************************************************************************
. *                                                       PART 2: Set codebook templates
. *******************************************************************************/
. 
.         cap log close
